Key Match Events: Namibia hold their nerve to secure super over win over Oman in a thrilling finish
David Wiese smashes the ball all around the ground in the super over and then comes back to bowl and seals a comfortable victory for Namibia who get their first points on the points table.
Post-Match Reflections: Namibia Captain - Gerhard Erasmus : Difficult to get momentum through the innings, we tried by getting the singles and doubles but every now and then we needed those boundaries which were difficult to execute. On a pitch like that, you need to take responsibillity after batting 15-20 balls, and you shouldn't allow new batters to face. In the Super Over we proved that there are runs to be had if you just assess the pitch well and take responsibility. (On Wiese bowling Super Over) David was up in the change room and he was very clear that he wanted to bowl the Super Over.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match is a tie!! We are heading to a super over.
